DMA Rank: 1 DMA rank from Nielsen 2015-2016.  DMA assignments are based on Nielsen 2013-2014 and may not reflect all subsequent changes in stations’ DMAs.
2 Interference component:  U.S. Constraints + Canadian Constraints * 2.3 (rounded to the nearest integer).
3 Station Volume=(Interference)0.5 * (Population)0.5.  If either a station's population or interference component equaled zero, we substituted a value of one.
4 Volumes scaled to the station with the highest volume in the UHF band whose volume was set equal to 1,000,000 (rounded to the nearest integer).

5 Opening prices calculated using the formula described in the Auction 1000 Bidding Procedures PN and in Appendix D of the Auction 1000 Application Procedures PN (rounded to the nearest integer).  "NA" means that the bid option or options are not available to this station because it is on a High or Low VHF channel.  “Not Needed” means the auction system has determined that this station will always have a feasible channel assignment in its pre-auction band at all of the possible auction clearing targets.
